<L>__{interior anne's cell day}
<A>__{anne looks out through a narrow window. her intense, fearful eyes flit and dart..}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{they're letting the crowds in.}
<C>__{mary}
<D>__{it's all right. you will be spared. the king as good as gave me his word.}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{the king saw you?}
<C>__{mary}
<D>__{yes.}
<A>__{anne manages a rueful smile..}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{we all made a mess of that, didn't we? we all underestimated little mary.}
<A>__{anne looks at mary..}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{i don't think he ever stopped loving you.}
<C>__{mary}
<D>__{that's not true.}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{it is. he never loved me in the same way. and deep down you know it.}
<A>__{mary averts her eyes..}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{you should have been queen. you even gave him a son. but instead all this has happened because..}
<P>__{(a beat)}
<D>__{because i couldn't bear to be the other boleyn girl.}
<A>__{anne shrugs..}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{and now look?}
<A>__{the sound of approaching footsteps. anne looks at mary, suddenly frightened..}
<C>__{anne}
<D>__{hold me..}
